Preheat a well-oiled #grill{} to medium heat. (TIP: If using a #grill pan{}, you'll heat it in Step 4.) Wash and dry produce.

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; dice into 1-inch pieces. In a #medium bowl{}, combine steak, one packet of @stir-fry sauce{9%ounce}, and a pinch of @pepper{}; stir to coat. Set aside.

Place @wooden skewers{8} in a #shallow dish{} and cover with water to soak (this helps prevent the skewers from burning!).

== Pork Meatballs ==

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens; mince whites.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, 1 TBSP stir-fry sauce, and 1 tsp water until a paste forms (use 2 TBSP stir-fry sauce and 2 tsp water for 4 servings).

Add @ground pork{10%ounce}, @sesame seeds{2%tablespoon}, scallion whites, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}; gently mix until combined. Form into 12 1-inch meatballs (24 meatballs for 4). Set aside.

== Jasmine Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1⁄4 cups water (2 1⁄4 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Skewers ==

Thread marinated steak and about half the @shishito peppers{8%ounce} onto skewers, alternating between one piece of steak and two peppers (we used four skewers; eight for 4 servings). Transfer to one side of a #baking sheet{}. Discard any remaining marinade.

Thread meatballs, @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}, and remaining shishito peppers onto skewers, alternating between meatballs, tomatoes, and shishitos, and tightly pressing meatballs around skewers to adhere (we used four skewers, eight for 4). (TIP: You may have some leftover shishitos! Feel free to add them to the ends of any of your assembled skewers or save for another use.) Transfer to empty side of baking sheet. (If using a grill pan, add a drizzle of @cooking oil{} and heat over medium heat now.)

Add skewers to hot grill (or grill pan). Close lid and grill until steak and meatballs are browned and cooked through and veggies are tender and lightly charred, ~{4-5%minutes} per side. (Work in batches if needed.)
> If using a grill pan, use a baking sheet or large metal bowl to create a lid; be sure to use an oven mitt or tongs to remove the hot lid.

Transfer skewers to a #large serving board{} or #platter{}; tent with #foil{} to keep warm.

== Cucumber Salad & Dippers ==

While skewers cook, trim and thinly slice @mini cucumber{1} into rounds. In a #small bowl{}, combine cucumber, scallion greens, @rice wine vinegar{1%tablespoon}, 1 tsp water, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir to combine.

In a separate small bowl, combine @katsu sauce{4%tablespoon} and @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}.

> Be sure to measure the vinegar—we sent more!

Fluff rice with a fork. Taste and season with salt if desired.

Serve skewers, rice, and cucumber salad family style with katsu mayo and remaining stir-fry sauce on the side for dipping.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

> Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.